---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 535
Tags:
  - Life-Love=Prayer-Meditation-Contemplation=On Concentration
By: Sri Ramakrishna
Glossary:
  - Term: kumbhaka
    Definition: Breath retention, a process in prânâyâma. or breath control.
---
When Arjuna was about to shoot at the target, the eye of a fish, his
eyes were fixed on the eye of the fish, and on nothing else. He didn't
even notice any part of the fish except the eye. In such a state the
breathing stops and one experiences kumbhaka.
